The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, August 23, 2004  LOOSE CHANGE
																								 SBI Life Insurance has launched Shield  a non-participating pure term policy with life cover at low cost. There is an option of increasing the sum assured over a period of time without the need for medical examination at each stage, while the premium payable remains constant throughout the term of the policy. Anyone between 18 and 60 years can take the policy, the maximum age cover being 65 years. The minimum and maximum term is five and 25 years and the sum assured varies from a minimum of Rs 3 lakh to a maximum of Rs 25 																								crore.																								 Syndicate Bank has relaxed certain norms for its education loan  SyndVidya. For loans up to an amount of Rs 4 lakh, the requirement for collateral or third party guarantee has been waived and for loans above Rs 4 lakh and up to Rs 7.5 lakh, no other security is required, except third-party guarantee and guarantee by parent or guardian.																								 Kotak Mutual Fund has unveiled the Kotak Opportunities Fund. The objective of the fund is to generate capital appreciation by investing in equity and equity-related instruments. The minimum investment is Rs 5,000 and the initial public offer will remain open till Wednesday.
